com.madisp.stupid

Class ExpressionFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.AbstractParseTreeVisitor<T>
      • com.madisp.stupid.gen.StupidBaseVisitor<Expression>
        • com.madisp.stupid.ExpressionFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StupidVisitor<Expression>, org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.ParseTreeVisitor<Expression>

    public class ExpressionFactory
extends StupidBaseVisitor<Expression>
    ExpressionFactory is used to parse a String into an Expression tree. Currently the underlying implementation uses ANTLR4, but this may change in the future. Note: Only the parseExpression(...) method is considered to be a part of the public API.
